   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Envirofit 2015. Direct Investment with Envirofit International Inc.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve policies, laws, regulations, and administrative practices affecting the private sector&apos;s ability to compete nationally and internationally. All the elements include not only the adoption and implementation of policies, but also their oversight by elected officials, NGOs, and the private sector. Improve the capacity of private sector entities to respond and link to markets. This Area includes work to link the poor to markets through effective and economically sustainable systems and relationships</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This award strives to generate rapid, sustained, and broad-based economic growth. More specifically, this includes a Production of clean cookstoves (2015 Project) http://go.usa.gov/cuvKJ. Direct loans to foreign private-sector enterprises from target countries, typically issued through a U.S. sponsor or borrower. The loan tenor is typically between 5 and 25 years, with a maximum of 30 years, depending on the type of project and its debt servicing capability. Interest and fees will vary depending on the project..</narrative>
  </description>
